<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sewer" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sewer</orth> (O. Edd. <emph>sure</emph> or <emph>shore</emph>) a drain to convey off water and filth: <bibl n="shak. tro 5.1.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 1, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.186" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 186</bibl>. Perhaps also in <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 71</bibl> (O. Edd. <emph>sieve</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>